From: Phil Staub <Phil.Staub@windriver.com>
Date: Mon, 4 Apr 2011 12:03:43 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 2/5] WRHV: Cavium: Update mac_addr_count

The mac_addr_count field of the virtualized octeon_bootinfo_struct
must be set to the number of available interfaces.

Signed-off-by: Phil Staub <Phil.Staub@windriver.com>
---
 arch/mips/kernel/vbi/wrhv.c |    3 +++
 1 files changed, 3 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/mips/kernel/vbi/wrhv.c b/arch/mips/kernel/vbi/wrhv.c
index 1b1cfda..266c24f 100644
--- a/arch/mips/kernel/vbi/wrhv.c
+++ b/arch/mips/kernel/vbi/wrhv.c
@@ -168,6 +168,9 @@ void __init octeon_boot_info_init(void)
  	octeon_bootinfo_struct.dram_size = VBI_MEM_SIZE_GET();
  	octeon_bootinfo_struct.eclock_hz = get_bsp_clock_freq();
  	octeon_bootinfo_struct.board_type = CVMX_BOARD_TYPE_CUST_WRHV_OCTEON;
+#ifdef CONFIG_CAVIUM_OCTEON2
+	octeon_bootinfo_struct.mac_addr_count = 2;
+#endif
  
  	memset(&octeon_boot_descriptor_struct, 0, sizeof(octeon_boot_descriptor_struct));
  
